{
  "schema_version": 1,
  "name": "Absolute Zero (OpenSky)",
  "mood": "Aether",
  "engines": [
    "OpenSky"
  ],
  "author": "XO_OX Designs",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "Sound frozen in crystal. All modulation removed: LFO depths at 0.0, no pitch envelope, no filter envelope. The supersaw stack at spread 0.15 creates a nearly static harmonic column. Shimmer at 0.55 with high feedback (0.75) and maximum damping (0.85) creates a reverb tail that is dark and frozen -- the high harmonics are absorbed, leaving only a warm, motionless resonance. The sound does not breathe, does not move, does not evolve. It simply exists. Poly count reduced to 2 voices for efficiency. The Guru says: stillness is not the absence of motion -- it is motion's destination.",
  "tags": [
    "opensky",
    "transcendental",
    "static",
    "frozen",
    "minimal",
    "motionless"
  ],
  "tier": "transcendental",
  "guru_bin": {
    "retreat": "OPENSKY Transcendental Vol 1",
    "retreat_date": "2026-03-19",
    "scripture": [
      "Verse 17: Maximum Damping Plus High Feedback Creates Dark Resonance",
      "Canon 7: Stillness in a Shimmer Engine Is a Radical Act"
    ],
    "revelation": "Parsimonia spoke: removing ALL modulation from a synth engine is the ultimate CPU gift -- zero modulation processing. And the resulting sound has a presence that moving sounds lack: it occupies its frequency space completely, without wavering.",
    "god": "Parsimonia",
    "flock_note": "The Ear described the sound as 'a warm glass column.' The Bone confirmed: with all LFO depths at 0, the per-sample modulation math is bypassed entirely. The Eye measured the spectrum and found it perfectly static -- no frequency movement at all across a 60-second sustain.",
    "diagnosis": "Absolute Zero is OPENSKY's contemplative extreme. In an engine designed for shimmer and movement, perfect stillness becomes the most surprising sound. The frozen shimmer reverb (high damping + high feedback) creates a paradox: a reverb that does not decay but does not ring."
  },
